        "details": {
            "description": "<p>The fetid material in this pit sloshes around in a disgusting feedback loop, filled with large pieces of solid trash that risk bludgeoning creatures inside it to death!</p>",
            "disable": "<p>@Check[acrobatics|dc:27] or @Check[thievery|dc:27] (trained) to move without causing a wave of filth, or @Check[athletics|dc:30] or @Check[crafting|dc:30] (trained) to stabilize the trash heap and prevent it from flowing; three successes are required to fully stabilize and disable the hazard.</p>",
            "isComplex": true,
            "level": {
                "value": 12
            },
            "publication": {
                "license": "ORC",
                "remaster": true,
                "title": "Pathfinder Adventure Path: Hell's Destiny"
            },
            "reset": "",
            "routine": "<p>(1 to 3 actions) The feedback flow hazard uses up to 3 actions to make flowing trash Strikes against living creatures that take move actions inside the refuse pit (area <strong>E7</strong>) but can only target an individual creature once per round. The ofalths, used to living in this pit, don't trigger these attacks. Additionally, any non-ofalth creature that ends its turn inside the refuse pit must attempt a @Check[fortitude|dc:36] save.</p><hr><p><strong>Critical Success</strong> The creature is unaffected.</p><p><strong>Success</strong> The creature is @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Sickened]{Sickened 1} until the end of its next turn, then is immune to this effect for 1 minute.</p><p><strong>Failure</strong> The creature is sickened 1.</p><p><strong>Critical Failure</strong> The creature is @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Sickened]{Sickened 2}.</p>"
        },
